node.text:
#makeup #vintage #60s 
A rare full makeup tutorial from 1969 narrated by makeup consultant Marla Craig. The model is Rena Alden. Though made in the late 1960's, the principles followed in this relaxing #makeuptutorial video still apply to this day. Many viewers also report that old #ASMR vibe too.
credits to: Glamourdaze on youtube.

node.title: take a look at one of my favorite 60s makeup tutorials. 💄📹 Vintage 1960s

node.text:
Icon, 🔥👑Michelle Pfeiffer as Selina Kyle/Catwoman in Batman Returns (1992)

Michelle Pfeiffer did her own whip stunts.

"I trained for months with the whip master. On our first day together, I caught his face with the whip and it drew blood. It completely shattered me. I was very nervous on my first day of shooting. I'd gotten pretty good with the whip, but when you show up, you don't having all the lights everywhere.” She completed her iconic "mannequin head strike" attack from the 1992 blockbuster in just a single take.

She was trained in whip combat by Anthony DeLongis.

"None of the other stunt girls got anywhere near her ability with the whip," DeLongis said.

node.text:
Katharine Hepburn falls into a canal in Campo San Barnaba, Venice, in this scene from Summertime (1955).@theclassicsdarling.
 .Although warned about the dangers of the polluted water in the canals, Hepburn insisted on doing her own stunt work. Passersby were informed that she was in fact an excellent swimmer, so they weren't to be alarmed when she tipped into the water. The scene was filmed 3 times, and as a consequence Hepburn contracted a bad eye infection which stuck with her for the rest of her life.
⠀
"I had no fear,” Hepburn later recalled. “but if I had known just how toxic the garbage in the canal was, or what kinds of problems it would produce for me for the rest of my life, I would have been afraid. I still wouldn't have let someone else do it for me, although it might not have been as hard on someone tougher-skinned than me. My skin has always been sensitive. I certainly would have put up a bigger squawk about it and suggested they use a dummy. As it was, they did use a dummy, and the dummy was me."
